Patch Set 4:

(1 comment)

James, are these warnings seen with '-Wall' alone or with some other flags? Could you also post the warnings that we're fixing here?


static inline int cl_io_type_is_valid(enum cl_io_type type)
{
        return CIT_READ <= type && type < CIT_OP_NR;
}

I think gcc is doing the wrong thing with enums here. The spec says that the compiler is free to use a signed or unsigned underlying type for enum cl_io_type (since in this case none of the enumeration constants have a negative value). So gcc should not be emitting warning based on its choice of using an unsigned type for the enum.

The grant changes are fine.
